Subject: Remove input_call_hotplug
From: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
Patch-mainline: Not yet (accepted by vojtech)

This patch introduces a new sysfs class 'input_device' as an abstraction
of struct input_dev. Thus we can get rid of the non-standard use of
call_usermodehelper and the input layer is compliant with LDM.
Greg KH is not too happy about it, but seems to have accepted it.

